column7: ('In 1985, Kung Fury, the toughest martial artist cop in Miami, goes back in time to kill the worst criminal of all time - Kung Führer, a.k.a. Adolf Hitler.',)

("Wallace lets out his spare room to a penguin. The penguin and Gromit, Wallace's dog, immediately don't see eye-to-eye. Meanwhile, Wallace has invented a giant pair of robotic trousers, designed to take Gromit for walks.",)
('Luis Buñuel and Salvador Dalí present 16 minutes of bizarre, surreal imagery.',)
('A group of astronomers go on an expedition to the Moon.',)
("Wallace's whirlwind romance with the owner of the local wool shop puts his head in a spin; Gromit is framed for sheep-rustling in a fiendish criminal plot.",)

("Wallace takes a break from trying to decide on a holiday destination only to find he has no cheese for his crackers. The solution to both problems is a trip to the moon, with dog Gromit, because everybody knows the moon's made of cheese.",)
('An office worker meets the girl of his dreams and uses a fleet of paper airplanes to get her attention.',)
('A prologue of one heart-breaking history of love and the prologue of the travel told in The Darjeeling Limited (2007).',)
("The story of a man forced to explore his memories in the wake of World War III's devastation, told through still images.",)
('A group of snooty birds roosting on a telephone wire get their just deserts when a goofy bird drops in.',)
('A hungry sandpiper hatchling ventures from her nest for the first time to dig for food by the shoreline. The problem is, the food is buried in the sand where scary waves roll up.',)
('Geri sets up a chess game to play his greatest opponent - himself.',)
("A stage magician's rabbit gets into a magical onstage brawl against his neglectful guardian with two magic hats.",)
('A Chinese-Canadian woman suffering from empty nest syndrome gets a second shot at motherhood when one of her handmade dumplings comes alive.',)
('The love life of a man as told through the meals he gives his adopted dog, Winston.',)
('Young Vincent Malloy dreams of being just like Vincent Price and loses himself in macabre daydreams which annoys his mother.',)

('Babies both human and beast are created up in the stratosphere, by the clouds themselves. One cloud specializes in "dangerous" babies, creating a challenge for his loyal stork that has to deliver them.',)
("A teenage alien is trying to abduct a sleeping human, but doesn't know which switch to use.",)
('A group of bandits stage a brazen train hold-up, only to find a determined posse hot on their heels.',)
column9: (["Gilbert M. 'Broncho Billy' Anderson", 'A.C. Abadie', 'George Barnes', 'Justus D. Barnes'],)

column7: ("The history of Nazi Germany's death camps of the Final Solution and the hellish world of dehumanization and death contained inside.",)
('Day encounters Night, a stranger of distinctly darker moods. But their suspicions soon turn to curiosity, and they are delighted to find the joys of their budding friendship.',)
('A red balloon with a mind of its own follows a little boy around the streets of Paris.',)
('In his squalid apartment, a man tries to squash with his shoe an insect of some kind that is moving around the room.',)
('Rapunzel and Flynn Rider have their wedding, but Pascal and Maximus must recover the rings they lose in mid-ceremony.',)
('Wallace and his dog, Gromit, open a bakery and get tied up with a murder mystery. But when Wallace falls in love, Gromit is left to solve the case.',)
('A story that takes place over millions of years and is inspired by the beauty of tropical islands and the allure of ocean volcanoes.',)
("Two buskers engage in a petty feud over a child's donation.",)
("On Anna's birthday, Elsa and Kristoff are determined to give her the best celebration ever, but Elsa's icy powers may put more than just the party at risk.",)
('At a New Millennium Eve party, Blackadder and Baldrick test their new time machine and ping pong through history encountering famous characters and changing events rather alarmingly.',)
("A fable of a young boy coming of age in the most peculiar of circumstances. It's the first time his Papa and Grandpa are taking him to work. Will he be able to find his own way?",)
('A snow globe snowman wants to join the other travel souvenirs in a hot party, but the glass dome that surrounds him gets in his way, despite all his efforts.',)
("A larger lamp watches while a smaller, younger lamp plays exuberantly with a ball but doesn't pick up the knack of correct handling.",)

("A sheep dances proudly in his southwestern landscape, until one day his wool is sheared and he is left naked. He's depressed and shy, until a cheerful jackalope comes along and shows him how to leap proudly and not to be ashamed.",)

('A woman returning home falls asleep and has vivid dreams that may or may not be happening in reality. Through repetitive images and complete mismatching of the objective view of time and space, her dark inner desires play out on-screen.',)
('A Christmas-themed special featuring characters from Walt Disney Pictures\' 53rd full-length animated motion picture, "Frozen (2013)".',)
('In the aftermath of tragedy, two grieving parents journey through an emotional void as they mourn the loss of a child.',)
('A black and bloody Irish comedy about a sad train journey where an older man, whose wife has died that morning, encounters a strange and possibly psychotic young oddball....',)
('A young boy sets out to revive his dead pet using the monstrous power of science.',)
('The classic Disney animated characters play the roles in this animated retelling of the Charles Dickens masterpiece.',)
('A train arrives at La Ciotat station.',)
('In a locked down train station, a homicide detective conducts an interview with a tormented monkey.',)
("If BURN-E (a welding robot) had known how much trouble he'd be caused by WALL-E's pursuit of EVE, then he'd have taken the day off.",)
('To save his house from rising flood waters, an old man uses bricks to build it higher, then he relives events from his past while searching for his dropped pipe.',)

('Ben is an art college student in London, whose imagination runs wild as he works the late-night shift at the local supermarket. What do he and his colleagues do to pass the long, endless hours of the night?',)
('A man trying to get home to his dog gets stuck in a time loop that forces him to relive a deadly run-in with a cop.',)
('A tin one-man-band toy tries to escape a destructive baby.',)
('In a short musical film directed by Paul Thomas Anderson, Thom Yorke of Radiohead scores and stars in a mind-bending visual piece. Best played loud.',)
column9: (['Thom Yorke', 'Dajana Roncione', 'Frida Dam Seidel', 'Joseba Yerro Izaguirre'],)

column7: ('Simon, a deeply religious man living in the 4th century, wants to be nearer to God so he climbs a column. The Devil wants him to come down to Earth and is trying to seduce him.',)
("Elmer Fudd is again hunting rabbits - only this time it's an opera. Wagner's Siegfried with Elmer as the titular hero and Bugs as Brunnhilde. They sing, they dance, they eat the scenery.",)
('David, an orderly at a hospital, tells his horrific story of being kidnapped and forced to play a vile game of survival.',)
